title: Fall In Love With Your Life
Why You So Sexy
paragraphs: Nature is the ultimate artist. It runs this crazy experiment with human genes. It mixes them and creates billions of looks. Amongst those looks are the ones that we describe as sexy. Looks that we, humans, are designed to respond positively to. And we do. We photograph those looks. We paint those looks. We film those looks. We describe them with words. We fight for them. We do unspeakable things for them. All as per nature's plan.
Nature, why are you so sexy?

title: My Favorite Adventure In Life
paragraphs: I am a professional beauty-discoverer. That's my favorite adventure in life. I love finding beauty. I love creating beauty. And it's a skill. You have a built-in sense of what's beautiful, but then - you develop it further throughout your life by encountering beauty that you haven't seen before. It's important to see beauty, to show your brain as many examples of beauty as possible, so it can mix everything it has seen together and create a new beauty. Just like nature does with mixing genes, a human mixes his visual discoveries and shapes his taste. Expose yourself to beauty. Develop your taste. And then leave the world more beautiful than you found it. 🤘🏻

title: Do It For You
paragraphs: I was listening to Jim Rohn’s record where he said something that was contrarian to the common wisdom. He said: "I will take care of me for you, if you will take care of you for me".

I often work with models who do photoshoots to take care of themselves. It’s an emotional care. It’s when you need to love yourself more. Photoshoots can give you that care. They raise your sense of self-esteem, self-confidence and self-love.
And they’re a way to have fun, when you’re bored of your daily routine.
And they’re a way to express yourself, when you can’t express enough going through days, weeks, months.
Whatever you do - take care of you for others. And ask others to take care of themselves for you.

title: It Takes Courage To Be You
She Knows When She Is Hot
paragraphs: Everyone has a badass angle. My job is to find it.

I work with women who are new to modelling. They do it for fun, for excitement, for attention, to express themselves, to discover themselves, to empower themselves. To show a middle finger to suppression, judgement and hate.

Every woman has her own reason for being in front of a camera. My job is to understand that reason and create an experience that she enjoys. At the end of the day, it's not really about the picture. The picture is an artifact that the model gets when she goes on a creative journey, called a photoshoot. The journey itself is why being in front of a camera is so enticing.

Every photographer offers their unique photoshoot journey. The journey that I offer is about discovering the badass feminine side of you. It's about stepping out of your comfort zone with your body. It's about being unapologically yourself. Revealing more than ever. Expressing more than ever. Becoming more self-aware than ever. Loving yourself more than ever. It's a challenging journey for most women. But it's the most meaningful one.

And it's the most meaningful one for me too. Knowing yourself as much as you can and living your truth as much as you can is what matters the most in life. It's called being a badass at life. When your photography helps with that, it's highly rewarding.
My job is to find your badass angle.

I am starting to believe in myself, believing I have a future and I can be who I want to be even as a stay at home mum. This photoshoot helped me, a lot... I pushed through boundaries I thought I never would, and I loved it - I felt sexy, empowered and on top of the world."

title: Accept Yourself
paragraphs: Accepting ourselves - that's hard for us, humans. Let's talk about it.

Why is it hard? Is it because others don't accept us? Is it because people on social media are telling us that we're not good enough? That our lives are not good enough? That what we like and don't like is not good enough?

Everybody's judging everybody, because nobody accepts themselves as they are. And here we are, on Instagram, carefully sharing crafted moments from our lives that we believe will please others. And in return - we hope, HOPE, that others will approve and love us a little bit more for what we broadcast in our Instagram stories.

Here's a real life story for you. This is Chrissy, and as you can tell from the pictures - Chrissy is gorgeous and sexy. The benefit of photographing people is that you get a chance to know them! Chrissy is smart. She's a nurse and she loves it! She enjoys travelling, healthy food and her passions are makeup artistry and modelling.

What you don't see on her Instagram stories is that Chrissy has sickle cell disease - Google that for a moment. Not a sexy thing to research? It scares people when they find out what it is. Yet, the first step to fight that disease is to face it, not to run away from it. And Chrissy's fighting!
I have a question for you - what are you running away from? What is that fight that you need to face in order to accept yourself?
Tell yourself the truth and then act on it.
And once you do - you won't need anyone's like on Instagram anymore. You won't need anyone's approval. You won't need anyone's permission to be yourself.
Because you'll have you, accepted and free to live your life to the fullest.
That's what I wish for all of you!

title: Wearing Emotions
paragraphs: What emotion are you wearing? What’s the brand? Who’s the designer? Where did you get it? How much was it? These are the questions that we’re not asking. We don’t talk about chasing emotions. We talk about chasing things and experiences that make us emotional.
We go on holidays to experience different emotions from the ones we experience in our office.
We do photoshoots to experience emotions too. Photoshoots offer rich emotional experience. You get emotions before the shoot, during the shoot and after the shoot.

I love photographing people with emotions. I want to style emotions with clothes. Or with the absence of clothes. With light or with the absence of light. With jewelry, sunglasses, plants... And anything else that creates the world for emotions to live in.
I want my models to experience new emotions. To build self-awareness, self-curiosity, self-excitement.
What emotions are you chasing right now?

title: I Met A Stranger

title: Creative Storm
paragraphs: This photograph was created outdoor in London at the beginning of October 2018. It was cold, +12C and rainy. When we've started photographing lingerie Lucy was all wet. We didn't plan the wet hair look. The weather added it's own style to our images.

What I've learned through this photoshoot experience is that there's very-little-to-no excuse not to create. Nothing was on our side when we were creating these images. The photoshoot was on Saturday's morning, Lucy's travel plan was disrupted by train operators, the weather turned from cloudy to pouring rain and it was one of the coldest days in the last couple of months.
Yet, Lucy and I wanted this photoshoot to happen and it did.

title: Leaving This World More Beautiful Than You Found It
paragraphs: How do you create a picture that is meaningful?

First, ask yourself what is meaningful to you as an artist? Leaving this world more beautiful than you found it. Beauty can make the struggles that we’re dealing with everyday more tolerable. What’s beautiful to you? That’s a tough question and to answer it you need to be radically honest with yourself and that’s not easy.

But what’s the alternative? Wasted time and regrets? No, thank you. So do the work of being honest with yourself, building your skills to be yourself and building your courage to stay yourself when the situation is challenging. And with that, go give everything that you have to the world around you, as the opportunity to give is limitless and the demand for beauty is infinite.

title: Your Body Shape Is Your Artwork
Think Lifetime
paragraphs: You’ve been doing this for years already, getting better, getting results, growing. I get it. Yet, understand that if you’re in your 20s or 30s or 40s or even 50s - this is just the beginning. You can start over again today and still have enough time to build something meaningful, fullfilling, beautiful and truly yours. With time you get experience and with experience you get a better chance of getting what you want. What do you want? Not this weekend. Not this month. Not this year. What do you want in this lifetime? Get crystal clear on that. Because that will be your guide through the most decisions that you will need to make this week, this month, this year.

title: All You Can See Is Confidence

paragraphs: Your trust is at the heart of my photography. I value it the most. It empowers my work. It makes it meaningful and valuable. Trust unlocks the side of you that is rarely expressed and almost never photographed. You have fears and insecurities, and so does everybody else. I understand. I don’t judge. I build trust that’s like a fresh air - lets you be you - freely and effortlessly. Confidence is built on trust.

title: Embrace Your Journey
paragraphs: Work.
How else do you think you’ll get it? But work smart. Don’t do mistakes that you can easily avoid by learning from people who already made those mistakes.

Read a book. Watch a video. Ask questions. Go do. Do it badly at first. Then do it again. This time better. Then again. And again. Better and better. Then all of a sudden you’ll be better than the most. You’ll be looked up to. You’ll be the inspiration. The role model. The hero.
Until then, embrace the work, embrace the inexperience, embrace the journey. On Monday, your journey starts again.

title: Get My Attention
paragraphs: Competition is real. The market is real. The fashion market is real. The dating market is real. The attention market is real. Before you get a chance to tell me anything - you need to get my attention. What gets people’s attention universally? Confidence. It’s seductive. It’s comforting. It’s optimistic. So if you want attention, if you want to stand out, if you want to be heard - express your confidence. Make moves that will make people around you wonder - who is she and why she has confidence to do what she does. Where did she get that confidence from and how can I get it too. And then inspire others to get theirs by telling your story. By lifting others up, by supporting them and giving advice when they ask for it. Get your confidence up and then help others to get theirs. All starts with attention.

title: Go Create

title: Courage To Be Yourself
paragraphs: Courage to be yourself is the ultimate superpower that you want to develop. Today, find the courage to do one more thing that is - you. Create what only you would create. Without compromise, without trying to fit into what others expect from you. Go genuine. Go be yourself.

title: Fear Of Rejection
paragraphs: Real talk here. The fear of rejection is damaging lives of so many talented and hardworking people. It’s stopping them or slowing them down from getting what would otherwise make them truly happy. Breaks my heart to see my friends suffering from it. What’s the cure? Getting comfortable with rejection. Going to the "rejection gym" and doing those "rejection push ups". What do I mean? Do all the right actions with the best intentions in mind and expect - a rejection. I know - it’s not fun, it’s not comfortable, it’s painful, but that’s how you grow your "rejection muscle". Doesn’t matter what you do in life - find a way to exercise your "rejection muscle". I’ll give you my example. I have a photography project - Boobs of London - that’s my "rejection gym". Good luck with asking women if they’re excited to get their boobs photographed and their intimate stories published. It’s a rejection, after rejection, after rejection. But that’s the point. The muscle is growing and with it - your chance of creating something remarkable. And quite frankly - just living a more fulfilling and happier life! So please, take some time off this weekend and brainstorm ideas of how you’re going to exercise your "rejection muscle". If you’re out of ideas - get in touch - I’ll help you out. With this post I am opening a "rejection gym". Everyone’s welcome. The membership is free.

title: Have No Regrets
paragraphs: What would you create if you wouldn’t be afraid of what others think of what you create? Would you be worried about that in 10 years? Would you care at all in 30 years? Would you have any regrets in 50 years? Tomorrow is a new day. A new week. A new opportunity to try new things. To go out of that comfort zone and explore. And if you’ll get a chance to talk to anyone in their 90s - ask them how do they feel about not doing what they wanted to do in their 20s, 30s, 40s... Don’t become that 90 year old. Create what you want today.
